## 3. Repair Process Pipeline

### Routing by Crash Severity

```
Vehicle Reception
      │
      ▼
  Crash Severity?
  ├─ HIGH ──► Mechanic ──► Straightening ──► Preparation to Paint
  └─ LOW  ──────────────► Straightening ──► Preparation to Paint
                                                    │
                                                    ▼
                                                Painting
                                                    │
                                                    ▼
                                                Assembly
                                                    │
                                                    ▼
                                               Polishing
                                                    │
                                                    ▼
                                           Quality Assurance
                                           ├─ PASS ──► Delivery
                                           └─ FAIL ──► ROLLBACK to ANY prior process
                                                       (with reason + manager approval)
```

> [!NOTE]
> QA fail — and any other rollback — can target **any** prior process in the pipeline, not just the immediately previous one. The mechanic selects the target process and provides a written reason.

### Process Table (DB-Seeded — Add new processes without code changes)

| Seq | Process Name | Condition |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Vehicle Reception | Always |
| 2 | Mechanic Work | High severity only |
| 3 | Straightening | Always |
| 4 | Preparation to Paint | Always |
| 5 | Painting | Always |
| 6 | Assembly | Always |
| 7 | Polishing | Always |
| 8 | Quality Assurance | Always |

---

## 4. Database Schema

### Tables Overview

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `customers` | Client data |
| `insurance_companies` | Insurer data |
| `vehicles` | Core entity; linked to customer + insurer |
| `processes` | Pipeline config (sequence, capacity, hours) |
| `process_logs` | Check-in/out timestamps per vehicle per process |
| `process_transitions` | Transit time between checkout of process A and checkin to B |
| `process_rollbacks` | Vehicle returns to prior step: who, why, when, target process |
| `findings` | Damage found during repair; cost, SLA timestamps |
| `parts` | Parts inventory |
| `suppliers` | Parts suppliers |
| `repair_parts_used` | Parts consumed per vehicle |
| `users` | Staff with roles (mechanic / manager / admin / insurance-viewer) |
| `notification_log` | Audit trail of every client WhatsApp/SMS sent |

### Key Fields

**`processes`** includes:
- `max_capacity` — how many vehicles the bay can hold simultaneously
- `sequence_order` — determines pipeline order
- `required_severity` — NULL = always; 'HIGH' = mechanic only

**`process_logs`** includes:
- `checkin_time`, `checkout_time` — primary KPI source for all stakeholders
- `actual_hours` vs. `estimated_hours` — variance = cost variance
- `status` — waiting / in_progress / completed / rolled_back

**`process_transitions`** includes:
- `transit_minutes` — time between checkout A and checkin B
- Captures whether delay is due to capacity (bay full) or staff (bay available but vehicle not moved)

**`findings`** includes:
- `reported_at` — when finding was recorded
- `insurance_acknowledged_at` — when insurer confirmed receipt (SLA KPI)
- `approved_at` — when budget was approved
- `cost_estimator_ref` — **nullable hook** for future AI cost estimator integration

**`process_rollbacks`** includes:
- `from_process_id`, `to_process_id` — can jump multiple steps back
- `reason` — mandatory text
- `approved_by`, `approved_at` — full audit trail

### Capacity Tracking

Each process has `max_capacity` (configurable). The system:
1. Shows **current occupancy vs. capacity** on the dashboard for each bay
2. When a vehicle checks out, the system checks if the next process has available space
3. If capacity is full → status shown as **"Waiting — Bay Full"** (capacity block)
4. If capacity is free but vehicle is not moved → timer flags as **"Waiting — Staff Delay"**
5. Both waiting reasons are logged in `process_logs.status` for reporting

---

## 5. Key Workflows

### 5.1 Check-in to a Process
```
Operator: Select vehicle → Select process → Click "Check In"
→ Creates PROCESS_LOG with checkin_time = now()
→ Sends client WhatsApp/SMS: "Vehicle has entered [Process Name]"
→ Dashboard refreshes: vehicle shows in that process bay with live timer
→ Bay occupancy counter increments
```

### 5.2 Check-out from a Process
```
Operator: Click "Check Out"
→ PROCESS_LOG: checkout_time = now(), actual_hours calculated
→ PROCESS_TRANSITION recorded: transit_minutes begins counting  
→ Client WhatsApp/SMS: "Vehicle completed [Process Name]"
→ Dashboard: vehicle moves to "In Transit" state
→ Bay occupancy counter decrements
```

### 5.3 Finding Discovered
```
Mechanic: "Report Finding"
→ findings_dialog: description, cost (manual for now), optional photo
   [Future hook: "Use Cost Estimator" button → will call AI engine]
→ FINDING created with reported_at = now()
→ Insurance Dashboard: immediately shows new finding alert (red badge)
→ Insurer views finding in their dashboard → clicks "Acknowledge"
   → insurance_acknowledged_at stamped (SLA measured)
→ Insurer approves budget → approved_at stamped
→ Repair continues
```

### 5.4 Process Rollback / QA Fail
```
Manager/QA: "Roll Back Vehicle"
→ rollback_dialog:
   - Select TARGET process (any prior, not just previous)
   - Write mandatory reason
→ Requires manager/admin role approval
→ PROCESS_ROLLBACK record created (from, to, reason, approved_by, approved_at)
→ New PROCESS_LOG checkin created at target process
→ Vehicle timeline shows rollback event clearly in history
→ Nothing is ever deleted — full audit trail
```

---

## 6. Stakeholder Views

### 6.1 Workshop Dashboard (Manager/Admin)
- Kanban board: one column per process, vehicle cards with elapsed timer
- Bay capacity indicators: e.g. "Painting: 2/3 bays used"
- Waiting vehicles: color-coded (capacity block vs. staff delay)
- Alerts panel: findings awaiting insurer acknowledgment
- Real-time auto-refresh every 30 seconds (`QTimer`)

### 6.2 Insurance Company Dashboard *(in-system, role-restricted)*
- Accessible via login with role `insurance-viewer`
- Each insurer sees **only their own vehicles**
- KPIs: check-in/out timestamps, actual vs. estimated time, time saved, cost reduction
- Findings queue: pending acknowledgment + budget approval
- SLA metrics: average time from finding → acknowledgment → approval
- No WhatsApp/SMS — the dashboard is their communication channel

### 6.3 Client Notifications (WhatsApp/SMS only)
- Check-in / check-out → automated message per process
- Finding discovered → "Additional work found, awaiting insurance approval"
- QA Pass → "Your vehicle is ready for pickup"
- All logged in `notification_log`

### 6.4 Workshop Floor Kiosk View
- Fullscreen PySide6 on any networked PC
- Shows all active vehicles, current process bay, elapsed time
- Color-coded: on-time (green), near deadline (amber), overdue (red)
- No PII displayed (license plate only, no names)

