## 7. Internationalization (i18n)

English and Spanish supported from day one. New languages can be added later without code changes.

| Tool | Role |
|---|---|
| `QTranslator` (Qt built-in) | Loads `.qm` translation file at runtime |
| `Qt Linguist` | Manages `.ts` source translation files |
| `lupdate` | Extracts all translatable strings from Python source |
| `lrelease` | Compiles `.ts` → `.qm` binary used by Qt |

**Implementation rule**: Every user-facing string in Python must use `self.tr("...")` or `QCoreApplication.translate(...)`. Never hardcode display text. This is enforced from the first line of UI code.

```
assets/
└── translations/
    ├── res_en.ts   ← English source
    ├── res_es.ts   ← Spanish source
    ├── res_en.qm   ← Compiled English binary
    └── res_es.qm   ← Compiled Spanish binary
```

Language switch is available in Settings — no restart required.

---

## 8. Code Documentation Standard

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Every module, class, and function must be documented.** This is a hard requirement to enable future debugging, maintenance, and onboarding of new developers.

Standard used: **Google-style docstrings** (readable without tools, works with IDEs and auto-doc generators).

```python
def checkin(self, vehicle_id: int, process_id: int, user_id: int) -> ProcessLog:
    """
    Records a vehicle checking in to a repair process.

    Creates a new ProcessLog entry with the current timestamp as
    checkin_time. Also decrements the available capacity counter for
    the target process bay.

    Args:
        vehicle_id: ID of the vehicle entering the process.
        process_id: ID of the repair process (from the processes table).
        user_id:    ID of the staff member performing the check-in.

    Returns:
        The newly created ProcessLog ORM object.

    Raises:
        CapacityFullError: If the target process bay has no available space.
        VehicleAlreadyInProcessError: If vehicle is already active in this process.
    """
```

---

## 9. Cybersecurity

| Threat | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| Password theft | `bcrypt` — never store plaintext passwords |
| SQL Injection | SQLAlchemy parameterized queries — no raw string SQL |
| Unauthorized access | Role-based: mechanic / manager / admin / insurance-viewer |
| Cross-role data leakage | Insurance users see **only their own company's vehicles** |
| Session hijacking | Session tokens with expiry; re-auth for sensitive actions |
| DB exposure | PostgreSQL on private LAN; cloud access via VPN or TLS |
| API key leakage | All credentials in `.env`, `.env` in `.gitignore` |
| Physical access | Kiosk shows no PII; portal requires login |
| Audit trail | Soft deletes only — no data is ever permanently removed |
| Backup & Recovery | Daily automated DB backup; quarterly restore test |

