## ✅ Plan Approved — Ready for Phase 1 Execution

---

## 12. Current Implementation Progress

As of the latest development pass, Phase 1 and the core Phase 2 workflows are
implemented for local desktop development:

- Workshop dashboard, vehicle registration, login, seeded process pipeline, and
  role-based navigation are in place.
- Findings can be reported from the dashboard and managed from the
  company-scoped insurance dashboard.
- Insurer actions are scoped to the requesting insurance company, and
  acknowledged findings remain visible until approved or rejected.
- Rollback is implemented through `core/rollback_manager.py`,
  `services/rollback_service.py`, and `ui/dialogs/rollback_dialog.py`.
- Rollback now requires manager/admin approval, a non-empty reason, a valid
  prior severity-applicable target process, and target bay capacity.
- Rollback updates are atomic: audit row, source log checkout, target log
  check-in, and transition record are committed together or rolled back
  together.

Verified regression coverage now includes focused findings and rollback tests.
The next implementation focus is broader process-engine correctness: one open
process log per vehicle, legal forward routing, waiting-state semantics, and
integration tests for the full repair lifecycle.
